                        <locus target="#">-</locus>
                        <desc>Drawings / decorations</desc>
                        <q>Decoration</q>
                        <note>Concentric circles drawn in red and black ink.</note>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <t:list xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                        <item xml:id="a2_553">
                           <locus target="#16r-29r-41v-54v-67v-80r-93r-104v. 118r-130v-143v-156v-170r-183v-199v">-16r, 29r, 41v, 54v, 67v, 80r, 93r, 104v. 118r, 130v, 143v, 156v, 170r, 183v, 199v</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">Ǧuz’ markers: al-ǧuz’ and the number in letters</q>
                           <desc>Drawings / Decorations</desc>
                           <note>The numbers given are 2-16.</note>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a0_553">
                           <locus target="#2r">-2r</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">List of abbreviations</q>
                           <desc>Marginalia</desc>
                           <note>The abbreviations refer to qirā’āt of the Qur’ān and are appear between the lines throughout the text.</note>
                           <note>
                              <term key="Koran" ana="#Koran"/>
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a1_553">
                           <locus target="#2v-3r">-2v-3r</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">Decorations</q>
                           <desc>Drawings / Decorations</desc>
                           <note>The opening has upper and lower panels with text in gold on red back ground with black floral decorations. The texts of the sūras are placed within a multiple circel in black, red and gold.</note>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                     </t:list>
                     <t:list xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#Inner lining of the front cover">-Inner lining of the front cover</locus>
                           <desc>Loose folio</desc>
                           <q>ما خرج من [السبيلين] [لاثة؟] عموم البشرية بالماء الطهور [...] ووجود ماء رقيق بعد النوم اذا لم يكن وعدم</q>
                           <note>Page from another manuscript</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#Loose paper">-Loose paper</locus>
                           <desc>Loose folio</desc>
                           <q>Text in Fidel script. Letter?</q>
                           <note>Paper with printed blue linings. The text is written with a blue ball-point pen.</note>
                        </item>
                     </t:list>
